transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Thank you for calling Viagra, I can help you today.

Speaker 2: Yeah.

Speaker 1: I'm on an automatic refill thing and I don't want to do that, I just want to call and order

Speaker 2: it when I'm ready.

Speaker 1: Got it.

Speaker 2: So, what I could do for you is I could set you up for every six month plan because every

Speaker 1: prescription needs to have a refill date to remain active.

Speaker 2: Without that, they'll actually be closed out and you wouldn't be able to order.

Speaker 1: But if it freezes out for you, you're always able to call us when you need it or call

Speaker 2: us to delay it.

Speaker 1: What's your zip code and your last name?

Speaker 2: 6-0-0-4-5.

Speaker 1: And your last name?

Speaker 2: Caree.

Speaker 1: P-E-A-R-R-E.

Speaker 2: And your first name?

Speaker 1: David.

Speaker 2: Okay, I pulled up your profile here, so I'll go ahead and I'll freeze it out for every

Speaker 1: six months, that way you can call us when you need it or call us to delay it.

Speaker 2: Other than that, sir, you won't be receiving anything monthly anymore.

Speaker 1: All right.

Speaker 2: Great.

Speaker 1: Thank you.

Speaker 2: Of course.

Speaker 1: Have a great day.

Speaker 2: Bye-bye now.
